dataset.title: NOAA NMFS Gulf of Mexico SEAMAP Scyphomedusae Data: 1985-2009

individualName.surName: Southeast Area Monitoring and Assessment Program

intellectualRights.para: Usage restricted to Global Jellies Working Group members.

section.title: Collection Methods
section.para: Scyphomedusae were collected using bottom trawls conducted at each SEAMAP groundfish/shrimp station. Medusae were assumed to be collected on the 'up' and 'down' cast of each trawl. The number of medusae were then counted in each trawl. For further information, please see 'Graham, W.M. 2001. Numerical increases and distributional shifts in Chrysaora quinquecirrha (Desor) and Aurelia aurita (Linne) (Cnidaria: Scyphozoa) and in the northern Gulf of Mexico. Hydrobiologia. v451(1-3): 97-111.'
